document_processor.py
Handles everything related to turning a PDF into something storable:
PDF file
    → convert each page to an image (pdf2image)
        → embed each page image using ColQwen2
            → return list of Page dataclass objects
It owns the ColQwen2 model — loads it once, uses it for both page embedding and query embedding. Nothing else touches the model.

vector_store.py
Handles everything related to talking to Weaviate:
Page objects → store in Weaviate
query embedding → search Weaviate → return SearchResult objects
It owns the Weaviate client and collection. It doesn't know anything about PDFs or ColQwen2 — it just stores and retrieves.
Gives you semantic, BM25, hybrid and filter based search.

rag_system.py
The coordinator — it doesn't do any work itself, it just connects the other two:
query (text)
    → calls document_processor to embed the query
        → calls vector_store to search with that embedding
            → returns SearchResult objects to whoever asked
This is the file the tools layer talks to. Tools never directly touch document_processor or vector_store — they only talk to rag_system.



!!!!!!dense (mean pooled) → HNSW ON  → fast approximate retrieval
THEN RERANKING with:
      colqwen (multi-vec) → HNSW OFF → brute force MaxSim only on candidates


      SO WE USE QDRANT AND COLQWEN2.5 3b multulingual on hugging face FOR RERANKING ONLY
The colqwen3.5 model uses ColQwen3_5 and ColQwen3_5Processor — if you switch to it later
just change the imports and add model.rope_deltas = None before embed_query forward pass as their model card warns.